benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: DELETE /1.0/kb/invoiceItems/{invoiceItemId}/tags - Remove tags from invoice item

covered: Valid Request scenarios (TC01, TC02, TC04, TC05, TC06, TC07) cover removing all tags, removing specific tags, handling no-tags scenarios, and behavior with extra parameters.
Error handling and edge cases (TC08, TC09, TC10, TC11, TC12, TC13) cover non-existent items, invalid formats, missing headers, invalid tokens, and service unavailability.
Header variations (TC03, TC15, TC18) cover additional headers like reason/comment and special character cases.
TagDef parameter variations (TC02, TC05, TC06, TC07, TC13, TC16) cover subset removals, empty/invalid values, and malformed inputs.
Performance/complexity considerations (TC17) address high concurrency, (TC19) integration availability, and (TC20) accessibility concerns.
gaps: Pagination: No tests cover pagination handling for large datasets or multiple pages of invoice items/tags.
Authorization scope beyond valid token: no explicit tests for 401/403 responses on unauthorized access beyond invalid token (TC11).
Rate Limiting: No tests to verify behavior under bursty or high-frequency request scenarios.
Caching Behavior: No tests checking for caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) or related caching behavior.
Soft/partial deletion semantics: no explicit tests around soft deletes or audit trails for deletions beyond basic error scenarios.
Explicit 403 responses or more granular authorization errors for user roles beyond token validity.
recommendations: Add pagination-focused tests to verify correct behavior and performance when invoice items have many tags or when listing is paginated.
Include explicit authorization tests for 401/403 scenarios beyond invalid token, including missing/insufficient permissions.
Add rate limiting/throttling tests to ensure the API handles bursts gracefully and respects quotas.
Introduce caching-related tests (ETag/Cache-Control) to validate correct caching headers and invalidation on mutations.
Add tests for soft-delete semantics or audit/logging verification to ensure traceability of tag removals, including per-user and timestamp checks.
